<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence from Philippe Sands QC</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence from </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">P</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">hilippe</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> S</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">ands</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> QC</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Professor of Law, University College London</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Matrix Chambers, London</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> (PCD 03)</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The House of Commons </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Political and Constitutional Affairs Committee </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> conducting an inquiry into Parliament’s role in conflict decisions, and has invited submissions to address the following question: </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Given the commitment made by the Foreign Secretary in March 2011, how can progress be made on enshrining in law the necessity of consulting Parliament on military action?</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">”</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">This </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">b</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ackground Note </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">proceeds on the basis that (1) a requirement to consult Parliament on military action will be enshrined in law, and (2) that in carrying out its responsibilities in any such consultation Parliament would have to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">act on an </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> informed </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">basis as to the legality of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">such military action</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. With this in mind, the Note </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">briefly </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">identifies the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">practise of the Government in informing Parliament on the legal</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ity of proposed military action in relation to two </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">international conflicts</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, namel</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">y</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Iraq (in 2003) and Syria (in 2013)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In both cases Parliament debated the matter on the basis of assertions by the Prime Minister of the day as to the legal advice that</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> had been given by the Attorney </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">General</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, supported by a summary of the legal argument on which reliance was being placed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. In both cases, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">assertions by the Prime Minister </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">did not appear to be an </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">accurate</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> summary or account of the legal advice received</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and in this way </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">had the effect of misleading Parliament</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. The consequence was </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a degrad</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">tion </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">lationship between the Ex</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">cutive and Parliament, and in the trust between the public and government.  If Parliament is to be consulted on military action, means have to be found to allow Parliament to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">form a proper view as to the legality of the proposed action. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">This Background Note follows on Written Evidence I gave the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">House of Commons Select </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Committee</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> on the Use of Force, in 2004</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">It </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">should be read against the background of the factual material set out </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in my book </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Lawless World</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(2006 editions, Chapters </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">10 and 12)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, and the evidence I submitted to the Chilcot Inquiry by letter dated 10 September 2010 (</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Annex 1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">)</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The provision of legal advice is important because the United Kingdom is committed to r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">specting the rule of law </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">as a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">matter</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">domestic</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> commitment and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in its int</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">rnational relations. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In practise, l</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">egal advice is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">first </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">offered to the Prime Minister and Foreign Minister, and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">then </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to the Government</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, ultimately by the Attorney General, who is the Government’s legal adviser</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref3"></a><a href="#_ftn3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Practice in relation to recent conflicts indicate that Parliamentary debate has been pre</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">dicated </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">on materials that have been tendered as </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">reflecting the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">“legal advice” </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of the Attorney-General</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, although this has not always been accurate (as indicated above)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In the absence of any ability on the part of Parliament to form its own view as to the legal issues relating to any military action, recent </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">practic</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e has tended to underm</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ine public confidence in the de</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ci</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">si</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">on-making process. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#1a1a1a; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#1a1a1a; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">(A) </span><span style="color:#1a1a1a; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Iraq </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">On the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">17</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of March 2003 the Attorney General </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">offered </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">one page answer </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(337 words) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to a P</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">arliamentary </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">question </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to the House of Lords</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">on the question </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of the legality of the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">use of force in relation to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Iraq war</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Annex 2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">).</span><a name="_ftnref4"></a><a href="#_ftn4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">It was later learned that t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he same </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">document</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">was </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">offered</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to the Cabinet on the same day, and characterised a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">‘advice’ to the Cabinet</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">document</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">provided </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">purported</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">outline</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">‘advice’ of Attorney General </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Lord Goldsmith</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">that the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">use of force by the UK in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Iraq would be in compliance with international law. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">It was subsequently learned that the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">document </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">was merely a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">‘view’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of the Attorney General, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and not </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">his </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">‘advice’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">or even a ‘summary’ of the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">full </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">legal advice he had offered </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the Prime Minister </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ten days earlier, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">on 7</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> March</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> 2003</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Further, it was learned that the document was written by committee, and that it was inconsistent with advice given by the Attorney General to the Prime Minister just a short time earlier. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> full legal advice </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of 7 March 2003 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">was not made available to the Cabinet</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">r to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">P</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">arliament</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (or </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">any Parli</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">mentary Committee</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, and was only </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">became </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">public in April 2005</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (Annex 3)</span><a name="_ftnref5"></a><a href="#_ftn5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; orphans:0; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The Prime Minister </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">addressed the House of Commons</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> on the 18</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> March 2003</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, and in my view offered the House an inaccurate and misleading account of the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">tenor of the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">legal advice he had received from the Attorney General</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The Prime Minister moved a resolution that</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">“</span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">notes the opinion of the Attorney General</span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> that, Iraq having failed to comply and Iraq being at the time of Resolution 1441 and continuing to be in material breach, the authority to use force under Resolution 678 has revived and so continues today</span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">”</span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref6"></a><a href="#_ftn6">[6]</a></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">This impl</span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">i</span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ed </span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">that the Attorney General had </span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">offered s</span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">uch an opinion</span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and had done so </span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">without caveat. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The publication of the full legal </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">advice </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in April 2005 confirmed that the document offered to the house two years earlier as </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">an </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">‘unequivocal’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">statement</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> that the war would be legal </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">was in fact nothing of the sort</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> his </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">legal </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">advice o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">f </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">7</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> March</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> 2003 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the Attorney General </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">offered </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a much more extensive exploration </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of the legal arguments, including the pros and cons, and concluded with an </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">equivocal position on</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the legal</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ity of the use of force </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">without an explicit further resolution by the Security Council</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">full </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">advice contained </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">important </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and necessary </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">qualifications</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> on the legality of the war</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> that were not made available to the Cabinet or Parliament. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In particular, the Attorney General </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">advised that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">“we cannot be certain that [legal arguments against the war] would not succeed”</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (Annex </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">3</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref7"></a><a href="#_ftn7">[7]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">This was </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">rather different to the apparently clear </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">legal endorsement of war that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the Prime Minister </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">presented to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Parliament</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> as </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">being the “opinion” </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of the Attorney General. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">n February 2005 th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e Attorney General stated that the document he offered in response </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Parliamentary</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> question </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">“did not purport to be a summary of my confidential advice to Government”</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Annex </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">5</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">)</span><a name="_ftnref8"></a><a href="#_ftn8">[8]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">is unfortunate </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">episode </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">undermined public confidence in the offices of the Prime Mini</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ster and Attorney General, and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">on the role and functioning of P</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">arliament. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">(B) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Syria </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Ten years after the war in Iraq a similar issue has arisen in relation to the use of force in Syria. The context is different, in the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">sense</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> that the legal basis for war is different: in relation to Iraq the purported legal justification was an </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">auth</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ori</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">zation</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> by the UN Security Council, whereas in Syria the legal justification </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">w</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">as</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to be </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the principle </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of ‘humanitarian intervention’, which is not well-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">established</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">international</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> law. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">advance of the debate in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the House of Commons </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">that took place on </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">29</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> August</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">2013 the government </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">issued a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">statement</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">”</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> which took the form of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> a short document </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">which outlined</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The UK government’s position regarding the legality of military action in Syria following the chemical weapons attack in eastern Damascus on 21 August 2013</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">”</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref9"></a><a href="#_ftn9">[9]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The document was </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">entitled “Chemical Weapon Use by Syrian Regime – UK Government Legal Position”, dated 29</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Aug</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">u</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">st 2013</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (Annex </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">6</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The document </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">concluded </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in paragraph 9 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">that in the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">circumstances that prevailed </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">“and as an exceptional measure on grounds of overwhelming humanitarian necessity, military intervention to strike specific targets with the aim of deterring and disrupting further such attacks would be necessary and proportionate and therefore legally justifiable</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">”</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">When I first saw the doc</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ument I noted that it </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">purported</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to set out “the UK Government’s position”, that it was unsigned, and that it made no reference to any advice or op</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">inion or ‘view’ of the Attorney-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">General. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> was therefore surprised when, i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">n the course of the debate </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in Parliament, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Prime Minister</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">referred to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">document </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">as </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a “summary of the legal advice” he </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">had </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">received from the Attorney–General</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Dominic Grieve</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">MP, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Annex </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">7</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">)</span><a name="_ftnref10"></a><a href="#_ftn10">[10]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">response to a question as to why he had </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">not publish the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Attorney-General’s full </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ad</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">vice (</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">put </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">by Caroline Lucas</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> MP) he </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">responded that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">what was published in the library of both Houses</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> represented a “clear summary” of the legal advice he had received</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref11"></a><a href="#_ftn11">[11]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Later h</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e went stated</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> that the coalition government marked a new standard of clarity and accountability by publishing “a very clear summary”</span><a name="_ftnref12"></a><a href="#_ftn12">[12]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I have not seen the full legal a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">dvice that</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the Attorney-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">General </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">presumably wrote </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and provided to the Prime Minister. I am therefore not in a position to express a clear view as to whether or not the Prime </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Minister</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> was accurate in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">characterizing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the document as a “summary of the legal advice”. Nevertheless</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, it would be a matter of considerable </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">surprise if the Attorney </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">General full advice w</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">as </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">as clear and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">unequivocal</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> as the view stated in the document of 29</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Au</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">gu</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">t 2013</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, given the controversy that still surrounds the principle of humanitarian intervention, and the strong opposition to it in certain quarters</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. The document made public and put before Parliament </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">resemble</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">d</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> an advocacy document </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(not unlike the 337 word answer to the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Parliamentary</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> question put before </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Parliament</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> on 17</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> March 2003), </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">not a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">summary of legal advice.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">It did no more than put forward the best available legal argument, but it was not presented in that way. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">It was ther</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">fo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">re unf</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ortunate that the Prime Minister should “</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">urge colleagues to read </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">this legal advice</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, which I have put in the Library of the House of Commons</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">”, and to state that “</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">this </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">advice</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> proves that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">[the use of military force] </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">would be legal</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">”</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">emphasis</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> added)</span><a name="_ftnref13"></a><a href="#_ftn13">[13]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Conclusion</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">It ap</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">pears that one of the lessons from Iraq has</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> not been learned. Once again, the legality of the use of force was an </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">important</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> aspect of the Parliamentary debate, and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">it appears that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the debate </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">may have </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">proceeded on the basis of a document </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">that was </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(on the basis of the information available to me) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">erroneously </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">tendered as reflecting </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the legal op</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">inion or advice of the Attorney </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">General.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="14" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">This underscores the need for a change in practise. On the basis that any use of force by the United Kingdom is to be debated in Parliament, and having regard to the need for Parliament to debate on </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the basis of a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">n informed </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">view of the legality of any possible use of force, steps need to be taken to enhance the way in which </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Parliament</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">informs</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> itself as to the legality of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">military action</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="15" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Assuming that the status quo is not maintained, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">then</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> it appears that a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">number of possibilities exist</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> that might allow Parliament to proceed on a more accurately informed basis as to the legality of any military action</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, including </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">inter alia</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">:</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(i)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the Attorney </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">General</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> makes </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">available to Parliament</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, or to a Committee of Parliament, the full legal advice he has offered the Government</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(ii)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Parliament </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(or a Committee of Parliament) obtains</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> its own legal advice as to the legality of any military action</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, from an independent source; </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(iii)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">individual Members of Parliament obtain legal advice from such independent sources as they consider appropriate.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="16" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">None of these options is free from d</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ifficulty</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. As to option (i), </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">it is important that the Attorney General must be able to prepare and then make available legal advice that explores all aspects of the matter in hand</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. (recognizing that legal advice will only rarely (if ever) be caveat-free or completely certain).</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Inevitably this will give rise to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">situations</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> in which certain evidence, and possibly legal argument and its assessment, cannot be put in the public domain</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (and should not be put in the public domain)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. There is a difficult balance to be struck between </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the need for Parliament to act in a properly informed manner, on the one hand, and a legal adviser to proceed on an appropriately </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">confidential</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> basis. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> As to option (ii), the possibility might arise that the Government and Parliament receive conflicting legal advice  (if this option were to be considered further, some thought might be given to the possibility that the Attorney General and a legal adviser to Parliament might confer to reach a co</span><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">mmon position, or elements of a common position). As to option (iii), this would inevitably result in competing legal views being put before Parliament.  </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="17" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In the circumstances, the most sensible way to make </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">progress on enshrining in law the necessity </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">for the Government to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">consult Parliament on military action</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">might</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">be for the Attorney General, Parliament and the Government to explore </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">appropriate </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">means </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">where</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">by Parliament can </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">proceed to a debate on the basis of an accurate understanding of the legal advice made available to Government, but which nevertheless respects appropriate confidentiality. If this is to be on the basis of a summary of legal advice, it should be an accurate summary. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The present situation, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in which the Prime Minister offers his own view as to the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">nature and effect of the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">advice of the Attorney </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">General</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, is regrettably not one that is likely to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">command broad public </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">confid</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">nce.  </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">4</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> October 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">TABLE OF ANNEXES</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Annex 1: </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Chilcot Inquiry by letter dated 10 September 2010 </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a href="http://www.iraqinquirydigest.org/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/PS-letter-to-Chilcot.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.iraqinquirydigest.org/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/PS-letter-to-Chilcot.pdf</span></a></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Annex 2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Answer to a Parliamentary Question, House of Lords, 17</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">March 2003 </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld200203/ldhansrd/vo030317/text/30317w01.htm#30317w01_sbhd3"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld200203/ldhansrd/vo030317/text/30317w01.htm#30317w01_sbhd3</span></a></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-49.65pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Annex</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">3</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">: </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Advice on the Legality of Military Action against Iraq without a fur</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ther</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Security Council Resolution</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, Attorney General, 7 March 2003 </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a href="http://www.globalpolicy.org/component/content/article/168/36072.html"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.globalpolicy.org/component/content/article/168/36072.html</span></a></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-49.65pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.2pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Annex 4</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Speech by Tony Blair to the House of Commons, 18 March 2003 </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200203/cmhansrd/vo030318/debtext/30318-06.htm#30318-06_head1"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200203/cmhansrd/vo030318/debtext/30318-06.htm#30318-06_head1</span></a></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.2pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Annex 5</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Statement from the Attorney General’s Office, 25 February 2005 </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld200405/ldhansrd/vo050228/text/50228w01.htm#50228w01_sbhd1"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld200405/ldhansrd/vo050228/text/50228w01.htm#50228w01_sbhd1</span></a></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-49.65pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Annex 6</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Chemical Weapon Use by Syrian Regime – UK government legal position, 29 August 2013 </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/chemical-weapon-use-by-syrian-regime-uk-government-legal-position/chemical-weapon-use-by-syrian-regime-uk-government-legal-position-html-version"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/chemical-weapon-use-by-syrian-regime-uk-government-legal-position/chemical-weapon-use-by-syrian-regime-uk-government-legal-position-html-version</span></a></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-49.65pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Annex 7</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Speech by David Cameron to the House of Commons 29 August 2013 </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">online: </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><a href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201314/cmhansrd/cm130829/debtext/130829-0001.htm"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201314/cmhansrd/cm130829/debtext/130829-0001.htm</span></a></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">Written</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">Evidence submitted by Professor Philippe Sands QC, Select Committee on Foreign Affairs, Minutes of Evidence, 1 June 2004: </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200304/cmselect/cmfaff/441/4060805.htm"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">h</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">ttp://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200304/cmselect/cmfaff/441/4060805.htm</span></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">; see also Examination of Witnesses, 8 June 2004 (Questions 264 – 279): </span><a href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200304/cmselect/cmfaff/441/4060810.htm"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200304/cmselect/cmfaff/441/4060810.htm</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">Letter from Professor Philippe Sands QC to the Chilcot Inquiry, 10 September 2010 (Annex 1)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn3"></a><a href="#_ftnref3">[